=== TASK ===
# Review, Edit & Iterative Revision Workflow

## Overview
Build an inline, block-based review and revision workflow for StudySpark that enables parents to edit generated content directly, request targeted AI revisions, track versions with a diff view, and approve final studies. The system supports autosave, optimistic UI, and conflict resolution for concurrent edits, with permission controls (parent-only edits and teacher collaboration when applicable). The feature integrates with existing pages page_p008 and page_p006 and aligns with the StudySpark AI-powered personalized study builder context.

## Components to Build
- Inline Block Editor (WYSIWYG)
  - Editable blocks representing study content (text, headings, lists, images, media)
  - Autosave per-block and per-document with versioned milestones
  - Block-level diff highlighting for revisions
- Revision Request Service
  - API to submit targeted revision prompts with block context (selected blocks, surrounding paragraphs, or entire section)
  - Support for different revision intents (clarify, expand, shorten, rephrase, upgrade difficulty, adjust tone)
  - Queueing, prioritization, and status tracking
- Version History & Diff Engine
  - Store immutable versions of the study content with metadata (author, timestamp, changes)
  - Diff visualization between versions at block granularity
  - Restore or roll back to previous versions
- Conflict Resolution & Optimistic UI
  - Real-time collaboration with optimistic updates
  - Conflict detection and merge strategy for concurrent edits
  - Visual conflict indicators and resolution flow
- Permissions & Collaboration Model
  - Parent-only edit rights; optional teacher collaboration with role-based access
  - Audit log for who edited what and when
- Study Management & Navigation
  - Save, duplicate, organize into folders, and share workflows
  - Progress indicators and autosave indicators
- UI/UX Components
  - Block toolbar, revision request modal, diff panel, version picker, and approval/merge actions
  - Inline edit affordances with accessible controls
- API Layer
  - Endpoints for blocks, revisions, versions, and approvals
  - Security, rate limiting, and input validation
- Data Persistence
  - Tables/models for studies, blocks, revisions, versions, approvals, users/roles

## Implementation Requirements

### Frontend
- Architecture
  - Component-based design using React with TypeScript
  - State management with React hooks and local optimistic state; consider a lightweight store (e.g., Zustand) for cross-component synchronization
